{"id":29587,"date":"2022-11-07T10:21:07","date_gmt":"2022-11-07T10:21:07","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wappier.com\/?p=29587"},"modified":"2022-11-11T11:53:36","modified_gmt":"2022-11-11T11:53:36","slug":"in-app-purchase-pricing-optimization-how-to-get-started","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wappier.com\/in-app-purchase-pricing-optimization-how-to-get-started\/","title":{"rendered":"How to get started with pricing optimization"},"content":{"rendered":"\t\t<div data-elementor-type=\"wp-post\" data-elementor-id=\"29587\" class=\"elementor elementor-29587\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-section-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-d51acdd elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"d51acdd\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-292a3e94\" data-id=\"292a3e94\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4a679639 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"4a679639\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><!-- wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><em><strong>In today\u2019s world, a one-size-fits-all payment strategy doesn\u2019t work. App users pay more for in-app purchases when the economic and psychological conditions are right. Ted Verani, vice president of global business development, wappier, shares a few key pricing lessons for app developers.<\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n<p>In 2010, William Poundstone explored\u00a0<a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/Priceless-Myth-Fair-Value-Advantage\/dp\/080909469X\/ref=tmm_hrd_swatch_0?_encoding=UTF8&amp;qid=1661520792&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">the history of marketing psychology<i class=\"fas fa-external-link-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\u00a0and found that one-size-fits-all pricing was a myth. \u201cMarketers and salespeople knew too well that what a customer was willing to pay was changeable,\u201d he wrote, \u201cand that there was money to be made from that fact.\u201d As a result, retail sales catalogs and newspaper flyers offered targeted discounts to customers, increasing sales in volume and transaction size.<\/p>\n<p>Mobile app developers can learn a great deal from the history of commercial pricing optimization. By calculating and predicting a user\u2019s willingness to complete in-app purchases, apps can offer personalized promotions that increase revenue. More importantly, developers can predict a user\u2019s lifetime value and automatically adjust engagement strategies on a moment-to-moment basis. It starts with understanding the varied nature of your customers.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-625ef13 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"625ef13\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p>Read the full story <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.spiceworks.com\/marketing\/mobile-marketing\/guest-article\/in-app-purchase-pricing-optimization\/\">here<\/a>.<\/strong><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-efee38f elementor-align-center elementor-widget elementor-widget-button\" data-id=\"efee38f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"button.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-button-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t<a href=\"\/lets-talk\" class=\"elementor-button-link elementor-button elementor-size-sm\" role=\"button\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Let's Talk<\/span>\n\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>In today\u2019s world, a one-size-fits-all payment strategy doesn\u2019t work. App users pay more for in-app purchases when the economic and psychological conditions are right. Ted Verani, vice president of global business development, wappier, shares a few key pricing lessons for app developers. In 2010, William Poundstone explored\u00a0the history of marketing psychology\u00a0and found that one-size-fits-all pricing [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":30864,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"om_disable_all_campaigns":false},"categories":[32],"tags":[123],"acf":[],"aioseo_notices":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/wappier.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/29587"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/wappier.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/wappier.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wappier.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embed